  "text": "## MVCC Compaction and Watch Stream Cancellation in etcd\n\nThe etcd implementation of MVCC (Multi-Version Concurrency Control) compaction involves periodic cleanup of old revisions and intelligent management of watch streams that span compacted revisions. The following describes the key components:\n\n### 1. Compaction Scheduling: Periodic vs Revision-based\n\nCompaction is scheduled through two modes configured via `--auto-compaction-mode`:\n\n**Periodic Compaction** (`server/etcdserver/api/v3compactor/periodic.go:Periodic`):\n- Records revisions periodically (every 1/10th of the retention period)\n- Executes compaction after the retention period has elapsed\n- For retention periods < 1 hour: compacts every X hours (e.g., 10m retention → compact every 10m)\n- For retention periods ≥ 1 hour: compacts every 1 hour\n- Implements exponential backoff retry on failure (lines 100-163)\n\n**Revision-based Compaction** (`server/etcdserver/api/v3compactor/revision.go:Revision`):\n- Compacts at a fixed interval (5 minutes via `revInterval`)\n- Retains a specified number of revisions from the current maximum revision\n- Calculates: `compactionRev = currentRev - retention` (lines 64-112)\n\nBoth implementations are created through the factory pattern in `server/etcdserver/api/v3compactor/compactor.go:New()` (lines 55-73), which routes to either periodic or revision-based compaction.\n\n### 2. Compaction of Revision Indices\n\n**Index Compaction** (`server/storage/mvcc/key_index.go`):\n- The `Compact()` method on `keyIndex` removes old revisions of keys\n- Processes the `generations` structure (lines 44-72 in key_index.go comments) which tracks key mutations\n- `doCompact()` (lines 258-282) walks through key generations and removes revisions <= compactionRev\n- Maintains `available` map to track which revisions should be kept\n\n**Backend Compaction** (`server/storage/mvcc/kvstore_compaction.go:scheduleCompaction`):\n- Iterates through backend storage in batches (lines 42-99)\n- Deletes entries with revisions that are not in the `keep` map (generated from index compaction)\n- Uses configurable batch limits via `CompactionBatchLimit` and sleep intervals via `CompactionSleepInterval`\n- Records metrics: `indexCompactionPauseMs`, `dbCompactionTotalMs`, `dbCompactionKeysCounter`, `dbCompactionLast`\n\n### 3. Notification of Watch Streams Spanning Compacted Revisions\n\nWhen a watcher's minimum revision falls below the compaction revision, it must be notified:\n\n**Watch Stream Cancellation** (`server/storage/mvcc/watcher_group.go:chooseAll`, lines 237-266):\n- During sync of unsynced watchers, `chooseAll()` checks if `w.minRev < compactRev`\n- Sends a `WatchResponse` with `CompactRevision: compactRev` (line 253)\n- Marks the watcher as `compacted = true` (line 254)\n- Removes the watcher from the group (line 255)\n- This notification tells clients their watch window has been compacted away\n\n**Watch Synchronization** (`server/storage/mvcc/watchable_store.go:syncWatchers`, lines 346-414):\n- Unsynced watchers are synced in batches (maxWatchersPerSync = 512)\n- Retrieves events from current store state and sends to watchers\n- Watches that couldn't send due to full channels become \"victims\" (lines 390-405)\n- Calls `slowWatcherGauge.Set()` to track slow watchers (line 411)\n\n**Victim Handling** (`server/storage/mvcc/watchable_store.go:moveVictims` and `syncVictimsLoop`, lines 257-339):\n- Maintains a list of blocked watchers (\"victims\") that couldn't receive events\n- Retries sending events to victims every 10ms (line 272)\n- Once successfully sent, moves watchers back to synced/unsynced groups\n- Decrements `slowWatcherGauge` when a slow watcher is no longer slow (line 324)\n\n### 4. Slow Watch Detection\n\nSlow watchers (watchers that fall behind) are tracked and managed:\n\n**Metrics** (`server/storage/mvcc/metrics.go`):\n- `slowWatcherGauge` (lines 87-94): Tracks total number of unsynced slow watchers\n- `pendingEventsGauge` (lines 105-112): Tracks pending events awaiting delivery\n- Updated during `syncWatchers()` at line 411 of watchable_store.go\n\n**Detection Mechanism** (`server/storage/mvcc/watchable_store.go`):\n- When a watcher's channel is full (can't send), it's marked as `victim = true` (line 505)\n- The slow watcher gauge is incremented (line 508) when moved to unsynced\n- The gauge is decremented (line 324) when the watcher recovers\n- Slow watchers are defined as unsynced watchers that haven't caught up to current revision\n\n### 5. Integration with Server\n\nThe compactor is integrated into the etcd server (`server/etcdserver/server.go`):\n- Field `compactor v3compactor.Compactor` (line 266) holds the active compactor\n- Created during server startup with `v3compactor.New()` \n- Runs in a background goroutine via `srv.compactor.Run()` (line 388)\n- Stopped via `compactor.Stop()` during graceful shutdown (line 962)\n\n### Key Files Summary\n\n1. **Compaction Scheduling**: `server/etcdserver/api/v3compactor/{compactor.go, periodic.go, revision.go}`\n2. **Compaction Implementation**: `server/storage/mvcc/{kvstore_compaction.go, key_index.go}`\n3. **Watch Stream Management**: `server/storage/mvcc/{watchable_store.go, watcher_group.go, watcher.go}`\n4. **Metrics and Monitoring**: `server/storage/mvcc/metrics.go`\n5. **Server Integration**: `server/etcdserver/server.go`\n"
